Habitat and biology
.

— 

Hemibagrus spilopterus

is found in a wide variety of lotic and lentic habitats. The species feeds predominantly on small fishes and crustaceans (Beeckman & de Bont, 1985; 
Rainboth, 1996
). In the Cambodian Mekong, it moves into the flooded forests to spawn, with the young being first seen in August; the fish migrate back towards the rivers in November–December (
Rainboth, 1996
).
